# Mirror — environment configuration
#
# This project supports two databases:
#   • SQLite   — for local development (file-based, zero setup)
#   • PostgreSQL — for production (Vercel + Neon, persistent on serverless)
#
# The active provider is chosen by which Prisma schema is used:
#   • Local dev  → prisma/schema.prisma      (provider = "sqlite")
#   • Production → prisma/schema.prod.prisma  (provider = "postgresql")
#
# Copy this file to .env and set ONE of the following.

# ── Local development (SQLite) ──────────────────────────────
# Path is resolved relative to the project root.
# After setting, run:  bun run db:push   then   bun run db:seed
DATABASE_URL=file:./db/custom.db

# ── Production (PostgreSQL on Neon, for Vercel) ─────────────
# Get this connection string from your Neon project dashboard.
# Paste it as the DATABASE_URL env var in Vercel (Project Settings →
# Environment Variables). The vercel-build script handles the rest.
#
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@ep-xxxx.region.aws.neon.tech/mirror?sslmode=require
